cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with WiFi network policy enforcement and airtime contention. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a likely category as the paper discusses enforcing policies for WiFi usage, which can have security implications. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper proposes a system for enforcing policies in WiFi networks. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper evaluates the performance of a real-world DASH video streaming application. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possible category as the paper deals with coordinating network-wide policy enforcement in a distributed system.
